The paper focuses on learning adaptable policies for robots, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The method proposed involves meta-learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves training a quadruped robot to walk, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
